{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01ETme7UXkcWHPx1WUBDEwnW","type":"tool_result","content":"1\tpackage trustmanager\n2\t\n3\timport (\n4\t\t\"os\"\n5\t\t\"time\"\n6\t\n7\t\t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/util/validation/field\"\n8\t)\n9\t\n10\tconst (\n11\t\t// trustManagerCommonName is the name commonly used for naming resources.\n12\t\ttrustManagerCommonName = \"cert-manager-trust-manager\"\n13\t\n14\t\t// ControllerName is the name of the controller used in logs and events.\n15\t\tControllerName = trustManagerCommonName + \"-controller\"\n16\t\n17\t\t// finalizer name for trustmanager.openshift.operator.io resource.\n18\t\tfinalizer = \"trustmanager.openshift.operator.io/\" + ControllerName\n19\t\n20\t\t// defaultRequeueTime is the default reconcile requeue time.\n21\t\tdefaultRequeueTime = time.Second * 30\n22\t\n23\t\t// trustManagerObjectName is the name of the trust-manager resource created by user.\n24\t\t// trust-manager CRD enforces name to be `cluster`.\n25\t\ttrustManagerObjectName = \"cluster\"\n26\t\n27\t\t// trustManagerImageNameEnvVarName is the environment variable key name\n28\t\t// containing the image name of the trust-manager as value.\n29\t\ttrustManagerImageNameEnvVarName = \"RELATED_IMAGE_CERT_MANAGER_TRUST_MANAGER\"\n30\t\n31\t\t// trustManagerImageVersionEnvVarName is the environment variable key name\n32\t\t// containing the image version of the trust-manager as value.\n33\t\ttrustManagerImageVersionEnvVarName = \"TRUSTMANAGER_OPERAND_IMAGE_VERSION\"\n34\t\n35\t\t// defaultTrustNamespace is the default namespace where trust-manager looks for trust sources.\n36\t\tdefaultTrustNamespace = \"cert-manager\"\n37\t\n38\t\t// operandNamespace is the namespace where trust-manager operand is deployed.\n39\t\toperandNamespace = \"cert-manager\"\n40\t\n41\t\t// fieldOwner is the field manager name used for Server-Side Apply operations.\n42\t\t// All resource reconcilers should use this to identify ownership of f