{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_vrtx_01BqUK3Nb8sbLuaiZEYomLbr","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I now have all the context needed. Here's the complete implementation.\n\n---\n\n## Complete Implementation\n\n### File 1: `pkg/operator/utils/apidiscovery.go`\n\nAdd the `NewProxyInformerIfAvailable` helper at the end of the file, after the existing `Applicable()` method:\n\n```go\n// pkg/operator/utils/apidiscovery.go\n// ADD the following import and function to the existing file.\n```\n\n**Add to imports** (the file already imports `\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime/schema\"` and `\"k8s.io/client-go/discovery\"`):\n\nNo new imports needed — the helper is generic and delegates to the existing `InitInformerIfAvailable`.\n\n**Add after line 91** (after the `Applicable()` method):\n\n```go\n// NewProxyInformerIfAvailable discovers whether config.openshift.io/v1 Proxy is\n// served by the cluster and, if so, initialises an informer factory for it.\n// It follows the same pattern as the Infrastructure informer in starter.go.\nfunc NewProxyInformerIfAvailable(\n\tdiscoveryClient discovery.DiscoveryInterface,\n\tinformerInitFunc func() interface{ Start(<-chan struct{}) },\n) (*OptionalInformer[interface{ Start(<-chan struct{}) }], error) {\n\tproxyGVR := schema.GroupVersionResource{\n\t\tGroup:    \"config.openshift.io\",\n\t\tVersion:  \"v1\",\n\t\tResource: \"proxies\",\n\t}\n\treturn InitInformerIfAvailable(\n\t\tNewResourceDiscoverer(proxyGVR, discoveryClient),\n\t\tinformerInitFunc,\n\t)\n}\n```\n\nWait — looking at the pattern more carefully, the infra informer is typed with `configinformers.SharedInformerFactory`. Let me match that exactly so the TrustManager controller can access `.Config().V1().Proxies()`. Let me revise to use the concrete type.\n\nActually, the cleanest approach is to keep `NewProxyInformerIfAvailable` parameterized the same way `InitInformerIfAvailable` is used in `starter.go` —