n## Design notes\n\n1. **`NewProxyInformerIfAvailable`** is a thin convenience wrapper over `InitInformerIfAvailable` \u2014 it hardcodes the `config.openshift.io/v1/proxies` GVR so callers don't repeat it. It preserves the generic type parameter so it can return the same `*OptionalInformer[configinformers.SharedInformerFactory]` type used for Infrastructure.\n\n2. **Threading**: The proxy `OptionalInformer` is created in `starter.go` (alongside the infra informer), stored in `ControllerConfig`, passed through `setupTrustManagerController` into `trustmanager.New`, and stored on the `Reconciler`.\n\n3. **Reconcile-time guard**: `clusterProxySettings()` checks `Applicable()` first \u2014 on non-OpenShift clusters this is a no-op. When available, it reads `Proxy \"cluster\"` from the lister cache (no API call) and returns the `.Status` fields, which reflect the effective proxy configuration after the cluster config operator has processed the spec. The `processReconcileRequest` method calls this and logs the settings at verbosity 2, making the proxy values available for downstream use (e.g., injecting env vars into the trust-manager deployment).", "stop_reason": "end_turn", "session_id": "a36c7296-0784-4af5-b840-7c5df961bda9", "total_cost_usd": 0.8656587500000001, "usage": {"input_tokens": 15, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 47349, "cache_read_input_tokens": 645705, "output_tokens": 9872, "server_tool_use": {"web_search_requests": 0, "web_fetch_requests": 0}, "service_tier": "standard", "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0, "ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 47349}, "inference_geo": "", "iterations": [], "speed": "standard"}, "modelUsage": {"claude-opus-4-6": {"inputTokens": 15, "outputTokens": 9872, "cacheReadInputTokens": 645705, "cacheCreationInputTokens": 47349, "webSearchRequests": 0, "costUSD": 0.8656587500000001, "contextWindow": 200000, "maxOutputTokens": 64000}}, "permission_denials": [], "terminal_reason": "completed", "fast_mode_state": "off", "uuid": "